==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fretted
<hw>Fret"ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. p. & a.</pos> <ety>[From 2d
<er>Fret</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Rubbed or worn away; chafed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Agitated; vexed; worried.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fretted</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fretted
<hw>Fret"ted</hw>, <pos>p. p. & a.</pos> <ety>[See 5th
<er>Fret</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Ornamented with fretwork;
furnished with frets; variegated; made rough on the surface.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Interlaced one with another; --
said of charges and ordinaries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fretten</ent>⟦br⟧
